#X text 48 146 First thing we need to worry is the number of voices. For a monophonic synth \, which is the most basic example \, we need a proper way to manage the monophony. This is provided by the [mono] object. Moreover \, we need a sound generator \, such as an oscillator and here we have the plainest one \, a sine wave. For last \, we need an envelope generator and here we have the most common one: an ADSR (Attack \, Decay \, Sustain \, Release)., f 50;
#X text 144 447 monophonic with a built in glide of 25 ms, f 23;
