#X text 448 31 You can refer back to the examples in the 'Control' part for more details on how to manage polyphony. This is done in Vanilla with [poly] and ELSE offers [voices]. Other than this \, historically \, you needed to have different subpatches for each voice \, but the most elegant and modern way to do this now is with [clone]. The [synth~] abstraction from ELSE offers a convenient way to set a basic synthesizer and it uses [clone] to load your synths.aIt can be mono or polyphonic. By default \, it loads a quite simple internal synth as a template \, a sawtooth and and ADSR.;
